<collectingCountry id="4CD56D97FF80404ECC06C89AFE2BFB37" box="[359,426,1159,1184]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">China</collectingCountry>
(Guangxi, Hainan).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7CD87E8CFF80404ECDA6C8B1FBF6FA9B" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="347D2D07FF80404ECDA6C8B1FBF6FA9B" blockId="11.[151,1437,151,1293]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="06B6F115FF80404ECDA6C8B1FEBAFB52" bold="true" box="[199,315,1196,1221]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="F3C25684FF80404ECEC0C8B1FC73FB52" box="[929,1010,1196,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Billaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="06B6F115FF80404ECEC0C8B1FC73FB52" box="[929,1010,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Billaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having fine black hairs on upper parafacial, 
<number id="820A3F20FF80404ECC77C8D2FEA5FB7F" box="[278,292,1231,1256]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="5.0">5</number>
distinct black longitudinal vittae on presutural scutum, reddish yellow femora and tibiae, abdomen translucent yellow, and gray white pruinosity only on anterior margin of tergites 
<number id="820A3F20FF80404EC97FC8E9FBADFA9B" box="[1054,1068,1268,1292]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="3.0">3</number>
and 
<number id="820A3F20FF80404EC903C8E9FBF2FA9B" box="[1122,1139,1268,1292]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="4.0">4</number>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
